tell you--when inventory finally gets back to the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">editor</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">three days later</TIMEX>--is
how many books have been ordered, not how many have been sold." Not until much
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">later</TIMEX> (<NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">as much as</NUMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">a year later</TIMEX>), after <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">bookstores</ENAMEX> have returned all their
unsold copies, can <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">publishers compile firm</ENAMEX> sales figures. And even then, the
